-- Cornell Suspends Men’s Lacrosse Team After Hazing Incident
-- B y   C h r i s   S t a i t i
-- 2013-09-20T12:45:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-20/cornell-suspends-men-s-lacrosse-team-after-hazing-incident.html
Cornell University suspended its
men’s lacrosse team, canceling all fall competitions, because of
a hazing incident.  Andy Noel, director of athletics for the Ithaca, New York-based university, announced the penalty in a statement
yesterday. The Cornell Daily Sun, the school’s student
newspaper, said the incident involved coerced underage drinking
involving freshmen.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Staiti at 
 cstaiti@bloomberg.net  